# {{substub}}
<nowiki>Leptonema is a name for the stage during meiotis Prophase 1 where the chromosomes condense after S-phase and interphase.
Leptonema results in the recombination of haploid(n) chromosome pairs with sister chromatids held by a single non-dividing centromeres.
Following the Leptonema stage is te Zygotene stage</nowiki>